Preheat your oven to 210°C. Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle over some @oil{}. Sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss. Peel the @garlic clove{1} and put on a small piece of #kitchen foil{}. Drizzle over 1 tsp of oil, wrap up and place on the tray with the fries. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{18-20%minutes}, turning halfway through. Remove the garlic halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Trim the @cucumber{1/2}(trimmed) then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}(trimmed) then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Zest and half the @lemon{1}(zested and halved). Pick the @mint{1/2}(leaves picked and finely chopped) leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks). Slice the @halloumi{250%g} lengthways into 4 pieces, half each piece.

With ~{10%minutes} left to go on the fries, heat a drizzle of oil in #large frying pan{} on a medium-high heat. Sprinkle the @smoked paprika{1%tsp} over both sides of the halloumi and fry until golden brown on each side, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. When golden, pour in the @honey{15%g} and give the halloumi a turn over the heat until glazed, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat and set aside.

When cool, crush the garlic on a #board{} with the back of a #fork{} or the side of a #knife{} to form a smooth paste. In a #medium bowl{} mix the crushed garlic, half of the @Greek style natural yoghurt{150%g}, lemon zest and half of the mint. Add a small drizzle of oil and season with salt and pepper to taste. Add the cucumber, tomatoes and lettuce to the bowl and mix well to dress the salad.

Mix the remaining yogurt with the @Zhoug style paste{50%g} and 1 tsp of water per person to make a thick but pourable sauce.

Place your @plain naans{2} in the oven for ~{2-3%minutes} to warm through. Share them between your plates and spread over a spoon of the zhoug yogurt. Top with a handful of salad, followed by 4 slices of halloumi per person on top. Drizzle over the remaining zhoug yogurt and sprinkle over the remaining mint. Serve the remaining sweet potato fries and salad on the side. Enjoy!